Singleton Scope	✅ Yes	@Repository ensures only one instance is created.
Thread Safety	✅ Yes	Spring automatically ensures only one instance is shared.
No Need for static	✅ Yes	Spring manages lifecycle, so static is unnecessary.

🚀 Final Takeaway

✔ You don’t need to manually create a Singleton—Spring does it for you.
✔ No static, no synchronized, just @Repository and constructor injection.
✔ This is the cleanest, simplest, and most production-ready version.

